Impact of Review Scores on Physical Game Sales

This is data gathered from vgchartz, metacritic, and igdb scraped using python using a scrapper that can be found here
Thankfully there are around 4,190 games that have review scores on metacritic, and sales data available vgchartz, unfortunately the data is measured in incriments of 10,000 sales so it is not as accurate as I would like. Digital sales are not included either so this analysis is strictly on physical sales.

Distribution of Data

Taking a look at the distribution of data its clear that it is highly skewed.

In order to analyze the data further I will take the log of total sales in order to normalize the distribution.

#Taking log of sales 
full_data_merged_plats$log_total_sales<-log(full_data_merged_plats$total_sales)

Review Scores

As an avid gamer I have first hand knowledge of some of the factors which impact video game sale. Critic and user scores are something that every gamer I know looks at before buying a game (and especially people buying games as a gift). This is univariate regression for both critic & user scores.

It does seem like aggragate critic review scores have an impact on game sales, albeit a small one

summary(avg_critic_scores_lm)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = log_total_sales ~ avg_critic_score, data = full_data_merged_plats)
## 
## Residuals:
##     Min      1Q  Median      3Q     Max 
## -4.3216 -0.9485  0.0574  1.0055  4.2423 
## 
## Coefficients:
##                  Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)    
## (Intercept)      9.765463   0.116058   84.14   <2e-16 ***
## avg_critic_score 0.040940   0.001654   24.75   <2e-16 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Residual standard error: 1.444 on 4187 degrees of freedom
## Multiple R-squared:  0.1276, Adjusted R-squared:  0.1274 
## F-statistic: 612.4 on 1 and 4187 DF,  p-value: < 2.2e-16

Number of platforms that a game is available on also have a big impact, since the majority of people only have one or two consoles. 

summary(num_plats_lm)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = log_total_sales ~ number_platforms, data = full_data_merged_plats)

## Multiple R-squared:  0.2293, Adjusted R-squared:  0.2291 
## F-statistic:  1246 on 1 and 4187 DF,  p-value: < 2.2e-16

Multiple linear regression

Combining the variables above along with genre, esrb rating, multiplayer, wether the game is a part of a series, developer and budget I will now try to build a model to predict a games sales. Since I cannot find a reliable source of game budget data I will use publishers since they are deeply involved with the funding.

summary(sales_model)
